Sentencas: Apatite-type lanthanum silicate based films have attracted significant interests to use as an electrolyte of solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) working at intermediate temperature.
Titulo: Fabrication of apatite-type lanthanum silicate films and anode supported solid oxide fuel cells using nano-sized printable paste

Sentencas: We have prepared Mg doped lanthanum silicate (MDLS) films on NiO-MDLS cermet substrates by spin coating and sintering of nano-sized printable paste made by beads miffing.
Titulo: Fabrication of apatite-type lanthanum silicate films and anode supported solid oxide fuel cells using nano-sized printable paste

Sentencas: Changes in crystal structure and microstructure of the paste films with the sintering temperature have been investigated to show that porous network structure with a grain growth evolves up to 1300 degrees C, whereas densification occurred above 1400 degrees C. Anode supported SOFCs using the pasted MDLS films were successfully fabricated: an open circuit voltage of 0.91 V and a maximum power density of 150 mW cm(-2) measured at 800 degrees C were obtained with the electrolyte film sintered at 1500 degrees
